    <item>
      <title>How To: Absurd Scientific Advice for Common Real-World Problems</title>
      <link>https://blog.jverkamp.com/2020/04/10/how-to-absurd-scientific-advice-for-common-real-world-problems/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 10 Apr 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://blog.jverkamp.com/2020/04/10/how-to-absurd-scientific-advice-for-common-real-world-problems/</guid>
      <description>&lt;figure class=&#34;cover-image&#34;&gt;
                &lt;a data-goodreads-type=&#34;book&#34; data-goodreads-id=&#34;42086897&#34; href=&#34;https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/42086897.how-to-absurd-scientific-advice-for-common-real-world-problems&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://blog.jverkamp.com/embeds/books/how-to-absurd-scientific-advice-for-common-real-world-problems.jpg&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
            &lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do not try any of this at home. The author of this book is an internet cartoonist, not a health or safety expert.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In a nutshell, &lt;a data-goodreads-type=&#34;author&#34; data-goodreads-id=&#34;19233943&#34; href=&#34;https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/19233943.randall-monroe&#34;&gt;Randall Monroe&lt;/a&gt; takes the humor that makes up &lt;a href=&#34;https://xkcd.com/&#34;&gt;xkcd&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=&#34;https://what-if.xkcd.com/&#34;&gt;what if&lt;/a&gt; series and turns it into a book series. It&amp;rsquo;s weird, it&amp;rsquo;s wonderful, and it&amp;rsquo;s worth a read. You might just learn something&amp;ndash; even if it&amp;rsquo;s not at all the thing you were expecting to learn.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    
