    <item>
      <title>This Is How You Lose the Time War</title>
      <link>https://blog.jverkamp.com/2020/04/06/this-is-how-you-lose-the-time-war/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 06 Apr 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://blog.jverkamp.com/2020/04/06/this-is-how-you-lose-the-time-war/</guid>
      <description>&lt;figure class=&#34;cover-image&#34;&gt;
                &lt;a data-goodreads-type=&#34;book&#34; data-goodreads-id=&#34;43352954&#34; href=&#34;https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/43352954.this-is-how-you-lose-the-time-war&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://blog.jverkamp.com/embeds/books/this-is-how-you-lose-the-time-war.jpg&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
            &lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Burn before reading.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A time travelling, spy versus spy, Romeo and Juliet-esqe love story with each of the two parts written by a different author (&lt;a data-goodreads-type=&#34;author&#34; data-goodreads-id=&#34;4175512&#34; href=&#34;https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/4175512.amal-el-mohtar&#34;&gt;Amal El- Mohtar&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a data-goodreads-type=&#34;author&#34; data-goodreads-id=&#34;3405346&#34; href=&#34;https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/3405346.max-gladstone&#34;&gt;Max Gladstone&lt;/a&gt;) as they travel through time and space and parallel realities, each trying to bend history and reality to the whim of their handlers&amp;hellip; all the while trying to hide their correspondence from the same.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    
